    "creation_date" : 1402840024,
    "answer_id" : 24230224,
    "question_id" : 8534178,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you want to replace a character in a String without leaving any empty space then you can achieve this by using StringBuilder. String is immutable object in java,you can not modify it.</p>\n\n<pre><code>String str = \"Hello\";\nStringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(str);\nsb.deleteCharAt(1); // to replace e character\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1827467,
      "reputation" : 4199,
      "user_id" : 1659790,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 73,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/sS2uf.png?s=256",
